question: Will Manchester City be the 2022-23 Premier League champions?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Manchester City F.C. is the 2022-23 Premier League champion. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

If it is a mathematical certainty this team will be the 2022-23 Premier League champion, the market will immediately resolve to "Yes." Likewise, if it becomes mathematically impossible for this team to be the 2022-23 Premier League champion, this market will immediately resolve to "No." Potential retroactive points deductions past these points will have no bearing on this market's resolution.

If the 2022-23 Premier League champion has not been determined by August 12, 2023, this market will resolve 50-50.

events.title: Premier League Champion
events.description: This is a market group over which team will win the 2022-23 Premier League championship.

question: Will OpenSea announce a token by March 31?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if OpenSea announces a token by March 31, 2023 11:59:59 PM ET, or to "No" otherwise.

"Announces a token by March 31" means they confirm by March 31 that they will have a token, regardless of when the token actually launches.

The resolution source is OpenSea (https://opensea.io/blog/, https://twitter.com/opensea, etc.).

question: Will the FDV of OpenSea's token be above $5b 1 week after launch?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Fully Diluted Valuation of OpenSea's token is above $5,000,000,000 1 week after launch. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

"1 week after launch" is defined as 12:00 PM ET, 7 calendar days after it launches. For example, if the token launches at 8 PM ET, March 15, then the FDV at 12:00 PM ET, March 22 will be used.

The resolution source for this market is CoinGecko, specifically the "Fully Diluted Valuation" metric. The FDV 1 week after launch will be memorialized on the Polymarket market description here: https://polymarket.com/market/will-the-fdv-of-openseas-token-be-above-5b-1-week-after-launch.

If OpenSea doesn't launch a token by December 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to 50-50.

question: Will $BLUR be above $1.00 on March 3?
description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if the Coinbase 1 minute candle for BLUR-USD titled 03 Mar '23 12:00 in the ET timezone (referring to 12:00 PM ET) has a final “Close” price of 1.0001 or higher, or to “No” otherwise.

The resolution source for this market is https://www.coinbase.com/, specifically the BLUR-USD “Close” prices currently available at https://www.coinbase.com/advanced-trade/BLUR-USD with “1m” and “Candles” selected on the top bar.

To see the “Close” prices, mouse over particular candles and look at the value after “C” at the top of the chart.

Please note that this market is about the price according to Coinbase BLUR-USD, not according to other sources or spot markets.
